habitat_description: Peromyscus keeni is a forest species of the Coastal and Cascades ranges in Washington State.  It has been considered a species limited to closed-canopy stands, but Gitzen and West (2002) found it in small canopy gaps and Taylor (1999) captured them in grass-forb, shrub-sapling, open sapling-pole, closed sapling-pole, and old-growth western hemlock forest stands in the Olympic Peninsula.
